# Falkyr auth (Clerk) — OPTIONAL.
#
# Leave unset → local mode: no auth, no external requests, the tool works
# exactly as before.
#
# To enable auth:
#   1. Create an application at https://dashboard.clerk.com (framework: React).
#   2. Copy the Publishable key (pk_test_... in dev, pk_live_... in prod).
#   3. cp web/.env.local.example web/.env.local  and paste it below.
#   4. Dev: restart `npm run ui:dev`.  Docker: rebuild with
#      docker compose build --build-arg VITE_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_... && docker compose up -d
#
# Note: the key is baked into the JS bundle at BUILD time (Vite), and it is a
# publishable (public) key — safe to expose, but rebuild after changing it.
VITE_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=
